['\n<h1>\n\t<img alt="" src="/system/files/5456/custom/monday.png?1684155545" style="width: 300px; height: 150px;" /></h1>\n<h1>\n\tmonday.com ICRA National Championships 2023 Incorporating J24 Nationals</h1>\n<h2>\n\tProtecting The Seas</h2>\n<p>\n\t<span id="docs-internal-guid-b3ed362b-7fff-848d-e484-565b5bdc3bf1" style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: &quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;; color: rgb(64, 69, 89); font-weight: 700; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span style="border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 167px; height: 200px;"><img height="200" src="data:image/png;base64," style="margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;" width="167" /></span></span></span></p>\n<p>\n\tHowth Yacht Club joined forces with our friends at <a href="https://www.sailorsforthesea.org/programs/clean-regattas/registered-events">Sailors For The Sea</a> in 2014. Since then, we have made as many regattas as possible cleaner.</p>\n<p>\n\tPlastic pollution, habitat destruction and depletion of marine life are just a few of the issues that sailors witness firsthand. At Sailors for the Sea Powered by Oceana, they unite sailors and boaters to take a stand for all oceans and waterways.</p>\n<p>\n\tFor the 2023 ICRA Nationals, we will try to achieve the Gold standard and that means we all need to make an effort.</p>\n<p>\n\tEvent organizers are placing a heavy emphasis on ditching single-use water bottles.</p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWe will not have single-use plastics.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWe will make sure our boat engines are turned off when we are not moving.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWe will walk or cycle and share cars to and from the event every day.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tPlastic-Free Dinnerware in the restaurant areas</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tEncourage use of Reusable Bags</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tResponsibly sourced prizes</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tProviding responsibly sourced meals</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tVegetarian availability</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tA &quot;Green Team&quot; on site</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tChoice of waste bins</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFood waste management</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tPaperless event management</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tEco-Smart Race Management</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tBlue Flag Marina standard toxins management</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tEncouraging &quot;green boating&quot; practices</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n\tThese small little things and others will combine to create one big result.</p>\n<p>\n\tNB: There is a water fountain near the entrance and tap water is freely available from the bar.<br />\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n']
